      • syncVDP

        public MigrationStatus.VDPstatus syncVDP(int vdpId,
                                SubscriberType type)
        Tries to change the status of the given VDP to SYNC. If it succeeds it returns SYNC.
        Parameters:
        vdpId - The VDP id that one wants to synchronize.
        type - The type of subscriber that is requesting to synchronize (e.g., SOURCE, DESTINATION, SYNC_ONLY). Notice that only the SOURCE subscriber will be able to change the status to SYNC.
        Returns:
        The VDPstatus after having applied the sync(type) transition to the state machine.

      • finish_syncVDP

        public MigrationStatus.VDPstatus finish_syncVDP(int vdpId)
        Tries to change the status of the given VDP after having performed the synchronization. If it succeeds it returns the status which resulted after having applied the finish_sync transition to the state machine.
        Parameters:
        vdpId - The VDP id that one wants to finish synchronizing.
        Returns:
        The VDPstatus after having applied the finish_sync transition to the state machine.

      • migrateVDP

        public MigrationStatus.VDPstatus migrateVDP(int vdpId)
        Tries to change the status of the given VDP to UNDER_MIGRATION, provided that the previous state was NOT_MIGRATED. If it succeeds it returns UNDER_MIGRATION.
        Parameters:
        vdpId - The VDP id that one wants to migrate.
        Returns:
        The VDPstatus after having applied the migrate transition to the state machine.

      • finish_migrateVDP

        public MigrationStatus.VDPstatus finish_migrateVDP(int vdpId)
        Tries to change the status of the given VDP to MIGRATED, provided that the previous state was UNDER_MIGRATION. If it succeeds it returns MIGRATED.
        Parameters:
        vdpId - The VDP id that one wants to finish migrating.
        Returns:
        The VDPstatus after having applied the finish_migration transition to the state machine.
